<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1911-12-01T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1911-12-01T00:00:00-05:00" n="1032" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d1032">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 892.001/78.</note>
                        <head><hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">President</gloss> to the
                                    <gloss type="to">King of Siam</gloss>.</hi></head>
                        <opener><seg rendition="#center">[Telegram.]</seg></opener>
                        <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">The
                                        White House</hi>,<lb/><hi rend="italic">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1911-12-01"><hi rend="italic">December 1,
                                1911</hi></date>.</dateline></opener>
                        <p>I extend to Your Majesty cordial felicitations on this auspicious
                            occasion and assure you of the friendship of the Government and people
                            of the United States and of their best wishes for the welfare of Your
                            Majesty and the happiness of the people over whom you have been called
                            to reign.</p>
                        <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">W. H. Taft.</hi></signed></closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>